  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Edward Morris Davis desires news. He regrets that William Lloyd Garrison is ill, but rejoices that he did not die. Edward M. Davis said: &quot;We have also been quite distressed about Mother &amp; Father [James and Lucretia Mott] who were both quite sick. Father has recovered but Mother has not.&quot; Davis goes on to tell about the western tour of his parents-in-law. Davis sends a few things for the fair.</subfield>
